definition.value: This is an AE which is a seizure in a baby younger than 4 weeks old. Seizures are abnormally excessive or synchronous neuronal activity in the brain.
This is an AE which is defined as having a temperature above the normal range due to an increase in the body's temperature set point occured on the neonatal.
This is an AE which is a rare but serious, even fatal, side effect that occurs in newborn infants (especially premature babies) following the accumulation of antibiotic chloramphenicol.
This is an AE which is different from the disorder affecting older children and adults.
This is an AE which is a medical condition where neonatal  body muscles contract and relax rapidly and repeatedly, resulting in uncontrolled shaking.
This is an AE which is a bacterial tetanus neonatorum infection characterized by muscle spasms.
This is an AE which is a condition in which the neonatal body or a region of the body is deprived of adequate oxygen supply at the tissue level.
This is an AE which is a neonatal state of strong desire for sleep, or sleeping for unusually long periods (compare hypersomnia).
This is an AE which due to renal tubular dysgenesis, secondary to the use of angiotensin converting enzyme inhibitor (ACEI) during pregnancy.
This is an AE which is the group of  neonatal symptoms that occur upon the abrupt discontinuation or decrease in the intake of medicational or recreational drugs.

This is an AE which is a complex task, as in newborns hypotonia can be the presenting sign of different underlying causes, including peripheral and central nervous system involvement and genetic and metabolic diseases.
This is an AE which is an involuntary, somewhat rhythmic, muscle contraction and relaxation involving oscillations or twitching movements of one or more neonatal body parts.
This is an AE which is the sudden unexplained death of a child of less than one year of age.

label.value: acute haemorrhagic edema of infancy AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is characterized by the rapid onset of annular purpuric lesions associated with initially localized edemas affecting the extremities.
This is an AE which is an uncommon-to-rare epileptic disorder in infants, children and adults.

label.value: reactive attachment disorder of infancy or early childhood AE

definition.value: This is an AE which is described in clinical literature as a severe and relatively uncommon disorder that can affect children.
This is an AE which is a infantile condition in which stomach contents rise up into the esophagus, resulting in either symptoms or complications.
This is an AE which due to appearance, is a type of benign vascular tumor or anomaly that affects babies.
This is an AE which is the excitatory ability that  infants have to respond to changes in their environment.
This is an AE which is defined as episodes of crying for more than three hours a day, for more than three days a week, for three weeks in an otherwise healthy child.
This is an AE which is a long-term inflammatory infantile disease of the airways of the lungs.
This is an AE which is an foetal abnormality of the structure of a body part.
This is an AE which is a condition during pregnancy or labor in which the fetus shows signs of inadequate oxygenation.
This is an AE which is defined as birth weight >4000 g and is associated with several maternal and fetal complications such as maternal birth canal trauma, shoulder dystocia, and perinatal asphyxia.
This is an AE which is a rare disease that is identified by an abnormally large or distended bladder.
This is an AE which is the loss of fetal blood cells into the maternal circulation.
This is an AE which is an abnormal growth that usually appears on a baby's neck or head.
This is an AE which is a common complication of pregnancy that has been associated with a variety of adverse perinatal outcomes.
This is an AE which is damage to the foetal body caused by an external force.

This is an AE which is irregular positions of the crown of the fetal head in relation to the mother's pelvis (the fetus is in an abnormal position).

This is an AE which encompasses a broad spectrum of disorders, united by impaired movement in utero.

label.value: preterm premature rupture of membranes AE

definition.value: This is an AE which defined as rupture of fetal membranes prior to 28 weeks of gestation, complicates approximately 0.4%-0.7% of all pregnancies.
This is an AE which is when the placenta separates early from the uterus, in other words separates before childbirth.
This is an AE which is often defined as the loss of more than 500 ml or 1,000 ml of blood within the first 24 hours following childbirth.
This is an AE which is among the leading causes of preventable maternal morbidity and mortality not only in developing countries but in developed countries as well.
This is an AE which is a type of mood disorder associated with childbirth, which can affect both sexes.
This is an AE which refers psychological trauma to the mother following childbirth.
This is an AE which is the culmination of one multiple pregnancy, wherein the mother gives birth to two or more offspring.
